cast.overview: Los Angeles, 1928. When single mother Christine Collins leaves for work, her son vanishes without a trace. Five months later, the police reunite mother and son. But when Christine suspects that the boy returned to her isn't her child, her quest for truth exposes a world of corruption.
cast.title: Changeling

details.biography: Jessica was born in Worcester, MA but moved to Hamilton, Ontario, Canada when she was 11. While in school, Jessica played basketball, was on Student Council and in the Dramatic Arts Club. She attended the University of Guelph in Guelph, Ontario, Canada with a double major in English and Theatre and a double minor in psychology and sociology. She started her career as an actor in the theatre (focusing on Shakespeare) playing such roles as Lady Macbeth and Juliet. She transitioned into television quickly with her first role on Queer As Folk. Jessica is represented by Actors Clearinghouse.
details.name: Jessica Irvine Drake
